    J Crohns Colitis
    A Systematic Review on the interest of Drug Tolerant assay in the monitoring of Inflammatory Bowel Disease.
Using drug-tolerant assays ADAb against infliximab (IFX) or adalimumab (ADM) can be detected during induction and predict primary non-response or LOR. Drug sensitive assays do not allow detection of ADAb during the induction phase as IFX or ADM concentration is typically high.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
Placebo response rates in randomized controlled trials for perianal Crohn's disease: A systematic review and meta-analysis.
Placebo response and remission rates in pCD trials are influenced by patient and disease-related factors, as well as the type of intervention being studied. These contemporary rates will inform trial design for novel therapeutics.
