Longitudinally, low -3 index was associated with greater Aß accumulation and WMS cognitive decline but unexpectedly with lower total ADAS-Cog cognitive decline. Although no associations were cross-sectionally found in the whole population, low -3 index was associated with lower WMS cognition and higher tau accumulation among ApoE e4 carriers. The Alzheimer's Disease Neuroimaging Initiative (ADNI) is registered at clinicaltrials.gov as NCT00106899.
